cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

The paper discusses the use of support vector machines (SVMs) in computer vision tasks, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a novel deep architecture for SVMs, which falls under the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper presents experiments on skeleton-based action recognition, which is a specific application of multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI, followed by cs.NE and cs.MM.
